1.title: Living with an Actor
1.plot: Not Everyone Can Just "Live with an actor"...it takes a lot of patience, and let me say A LOT. Coming from various backgrounds, instructors, methods, and everything else that comes with the wood works of an actor, creates a perfect form of torture some may say. Come and take a glimpse of how it is for some people..daily tolerating..living with an actor.

2.title: If Humans Behaved Like Animals
2.plot: What would happen if humans behaved like animals? How would the world perceive us? Would they be amused, shocked, scared, start behaving like ones themselves, or not even phased? Take a glimpse into the daily lives of California residents, as they experience their roommates behaving like animals.

3.title: Florida Vs. California: The Pros and Cons
3.plot: For centuries, time after time, many have argued what makes "Florida" so great, or what makes "California" so great. Ironically, many cast members from "Shenanigans" have lived in both California and Florida, whereas, some have only lived in only one of the two states and mayyybe visited the other, while many are true natives to one or the other. So, if one was looking for advice as to where to live, where should they live? Are there Pros and Cons of both? Come and explore the brains, the experience of true natives (and non ) alike. Let the games, urr, I mean battles ...
